title._content: Illustrated front cover from The Queenslander December 17 1936

description._content: Photographer: unidentified Location: Description:Caption: It is easier to type than write - own a Corona. MacDougalls (Q'land) Pty Ltd., Queen St., Brisbane. The cover of christmas issue of the Queenslander features Santa, his sleigh and reindeer. Santa carries a large sack of presents over one shoulder and has a briefcase in his other hand. The sleigh too is loaded with presents including dolls and a typewriter.
